
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gst-discoverer-1.0` baraye kashf va namayeshe etela'at darbareye file-haye multimedia (mesle video va audio) estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad ta format, codec-ha, va etela'ate digar raje' be media-ye khod ra bedanid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--version` --> ℹ️ Namayesh version-e `gst-discoverer-1.0`
    🔹 `--help`    --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye estefade az dastoor
    🔹 `<URI>`       --> 🔗 Address-e file ya stream-e multimedia baraye kashf

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gst-discoverer-1.0 file:///path/to/your/video.mp4

    🔹 Keshf va namayeshe etela'at darbareye yek file video-ye mahali.

    $ gst-discoverer-1.0 https://example.com/your/audio.mp3

    🔹 Keshf va namayeshe etela'at darbareye yek stream audio az yek URL.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gst-discoverer-1.0 file:///home/user/myvideo.avi

    🔹 Ba ejraye in dastoor, etela'ati mesle format, codec-haye estefade shode, tool va arz video, va etela'ate audio namayesh dade mishavand.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gst-discoverer-1.0` command is used to discover and display information about multimedia files (like video and audio). This command helps you find out the format, codecs, and other information about your media.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--version` --> ℹ️ Display the version of `gst-discoverer-1.0`
    🔹 `--help`    --> ❓ Display help information for the command
    🔹 `<URI>`       --> 🔗 The address of the multimedia file or stream to discover

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gst-discoverer-1.0 file:///path/to/your/video.mp4

    🔹 Discover and display information about a local video file.

    $ gst-discoverer-1.0 https://example.com/your/audio.mp3

    🔹 Discover and display information about an audio stream from a URL.

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ gst-discoverer-1.0 file:///home/user/myvideo.avi

    🔹 By running this command, information such as the format, codecs used, video width and height, and audio information will be displayed.
